A. Evaluation Rubrics 

1. Understanding of the Dataset and Data Sources 
o Nature of the data 
o Type of attributes 
o Real-world relevance 
2. Input and Output Specification 
o Clearly defined features and target variable 
o Problem formulation 
3. Mathematical Modeling 
o Mathematical formulation of the problem 
o Variables involved 
o Optimization techniques used 
4. Computational Steps 
o Step-by-step explanation of the selected model 
o Pipeline clarity 
5. Coding Proficiency 
o Code readability 
o Proper use of libraries and functions 
B. Problem Statement 
A healthcare analytics company has collected a dataset to predict whether a patient is at 
high risk of developing a chronic disease. 
Dataset Description 
The dataset contains the following attributes: 
 Patient_ID 
 Age 
 Gender 
 Blood_Pressure (contains missing values) 
 Cholesterol_Level (contains extreme values / outliers) 
 Hospital_Visits_Per_Year 
 Smoking_Status 
 Exercise_Level 
 Medical_Notes (free-text data) 
 Wearable_Sensor_Data (time-series data) 
 Disease_Risk (binary target variable; highly imbalanced)
C. Tasks to be Performed 
1. Data Understanding and Pre-processing 
o Identify data types (numerical, categorical, text, time-series). 
o Perform encoding wherever required (with justification). 
2. Missing Value Handling 
o Apply an appropriate missing value imputation technique. 
o Justify the choice of method based on data characteristics. 
3. Class Imbalance Handling 
o Address the class imbalance problem using a suitable technique. 
o Justify why the chosen method is appropriate. 
4. Outlier Detection and Treatment 
o Detect outliers in relevant features. 
o Apply a suitable outlier handling method with justification. 
5. Feature Scaling 
o Perform normalization or standardization. 
6. Feature Selection / Dimensionality Reduction 
Apply and compare the following methods: 
o Variance-based feature selection 
o Information Gain 
o Forward Feature Selection 
o Principal Component Analysis (PCA) 
7. Model Building 
o Apply Logistic Regression for classification.. 
8. Comparative Study 
o Compare Logistic Regression performance with: 
 No feature selection 
 Variance method 
 Information Gain 
 Forward Selection 
 PCA 
o Present results in a tabular format using F1-Score as the primary evaluation 
metric.
